Its Mothers day.

its been almost 7 months since my mother was killed.

she was my guide in this world.

since her passing ive not been the same.

when i need advice i feel hollow and alone because the one person who has ever loved me unconditionally is gone from this world robbed from me and all the people who loved her dearly by a person who was too busy paying attention to the radio to stay in the proper traffic lane.

seven months and still i feel like there is a void in my life ... seven months ... before she passed i put her email off for a week because i wasnt in the mood to respond ...

heaven has to exist, for her, or my world my colapse around me at any time.

I just want to go home... but that died with my mother.

I cant help but be haunted by the fact that if i hadnt moved to az i would have been in that car.

I cant sleep right now because the nightmares will come again.

I wish i had told her i loved her more often remember people its something that u can never say too much.

There is no justice left in this world.

she was always trying to help me meet the right girl, and now when i do meet the right girl who isnt taken, she ll never get to meet her.

i must have been a wonderful person in a former life to have her as my mother.

I hope, that she is at peace, and maybe someday i can be too.

I love u Mom be at peace.

-Darryl

welcome to the urban jungle there are no fun and game everywhere u look u find another forgotten name. u know i really feel like this place is smothering me sometimes maybe its just the job who knows it all just seems to blur toghether anymore day night week year does it really matter when there are so few times u feel at peace surrounded by the glow of the people u associate with? its so annoying to go out and have fun and then look back and be depressed about it because its the most fun u have had in years and u know it will be along time before u touch the beach of that island of peace again. smothered in a sea of inane bullshit surrounded by the comforts of modern living and yet left with no peace. i think that may be my new banner no peace dont think there really is such a thing but im to stubborn to give in at the same time really quite annoying this whole spinning ball of rot. i would also like to say to any who see this believe not the lies money is not happyness money is simply a distraction from the pain between moments of bliss and in the end it simply buys u ignorance.
